  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav) translates to \"discrimination\" or \"differentiation\" in English. It refers to the practice of treating people unfairly or differently based on certain characteristics such as caste, gender, religion, or other attributes. Bhedbhaav often implies a negative connotation, highlighting injustices and inequalities in society.",
